</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-216_"><b>Helps men and women:</b> Many hair loss treatments work much better for men than they do for women, but that’s not the case with red light therapy. Research shows that this technology is effective regardless of gender.  
 
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-218_"><b>It doesn’t hurt: </b>Some treatments for hair loss, like restoration surgery, microneedling, and PRP, can be quite painful. Red light therapy is a gentle, non-invasive option that doesn’t hurt at all. 
  
 
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-298_"><b>It can be combined with other treatments: </b>When you’re dealing with hair loss, chances are you want to do everything in your power to combat it. Because red light therapy is so gentle and non-invasive, you can combine it with other hair loss treatments to ensure a better outcome. 
 
  
 
